article.headline: Norfolk State 74, Maryland-Eastern Shore 62
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Calvin Brown scored 18 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Norfolk State beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 74-62 Wednesday night. The two teams were tied at 35 at halftime, but Norfolk State went on a run in the second half after Antonio McMillion landed a free-throw to give UMES a 47-45 lead. Norfolk then outscored UMES 13-2 over five minutes to take a 12-point lead with just over eight minutes to play. Tynell Dunkley added 16 points and Tony Murphy had 15 points for Norfolk State (2-9, 2-0 MEAC). Ed Tyson and Antonio McMillion each scored 17 points for UMES (2-11, 0-2).
